text:
So I went to Ulta yesterday because it's one of my most favorite places and I was ready to spend over $1,000! I wanted hair extensions and make-up. Easy enough right? Wrong! Not at this location!! First off there was only one person working the salon I sat there for 20 minutes only to be told the girl isn't there. So I didn't even get any information. Next I went  go and get my Clinique. I stood there for another 20 minutes and no one helped me. I wandered around until I found help and the woman was really sweet but refused to even go to Clinique and was insistent on selling me Torte. It's a great product,  just not what I wanted. Needless to say, I left empty handed. I've scheduled my hair elsewhere and probably be going to Sephora for my make-up.
